1
00:00:05,588 --> 00:00:07,465
(game clock audio) 30 seconds

2
00:00:15,598 --> 00:00:17,392
40 seconds

3
00:00:25,608 --> 00:00:30,572
50 seconds 1 2 3 4…

4
00:00:44,419 --> 00:00:45,462
(sound of water drops)

5
00:00:57,849 --> 00:01:01,603
(sound of sliding door opening and closing)

6
00:01:41,142 --> 00:01:42,227
(Tatsumi) “Caused the divorce⸺”

7
00:01:42,310 --> 00:01:44,562
“Claim for compensation from cheating partner”

8
00:01:46,105 --> 00:01:47,398
(Kotaro) Wait... what are you looking at without permission?

9
00:01:47,482 --> 00:01:51,111
Sorry, I just noticed it

10
00:01:56,658 --> 00:02:01,287
(mobile phone vibrator)

11
00:02:02,705 --> 00:02:04,457
(Torataro) Hello, Toshie-san?

12
00:02:04,541 --> 00:02:06,626
No, the court hasn't started yet.

13
00:02:06,709 --> 00:02:09,337
Huh! ? Did Professor Yamamoto resign?

14
00:02:09,420 --> 00:02:12,298
Well... that would be a problem though.

15
00:02:12,382 --> 00:02:14,592
The court is about to open...

16
00:02:14,676 --> 00:02:18,012
Ah, I understand. I understand. I'll ask you more details when I get back.

17
00:02:18,596 --> 00:02:21,599
Then ha...

18
00:02:24,269 --> 00:02:25,603
Wait... what are you doing!

19
00:02:25,687 --> 00:02:26,646
(Tatsumi) Sorry.

20
00:02:26,729 --> 00:02:30,191
But, uh...maybe it's unnecessary, but...

21
00:02:32,819 --> 00:02:35,363
-(Tatsumi) What is this?-(Torataro) What is this? this

22
00:02:35,446 --> 00:02:39,659
It's a blocker. Please watch it after today's game is over.

23
00:02:43,746 --> 00:02:45,290
Fuujite?

24
00:02:46,207 --> 00:02:48,251
(Clerk) You are the plaintiff's attorney, right?

25
00:02:48,334 --> 00:02:50,086
The court will open soon

26
00:02:53,173 --> 00:02:56,217
Yes I'll go

27
00:02:59,179 --> 00:03:01,764
(Torataro) I'm sorry!

28
00:03:01,848 --> 00:03:04,684
(Female) What does zero alimony mean?

29
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:10,231
The court ruled that the reason for divorce was not the husband's cheating.

30
00:03:10,315 --> 00:03:14,319
Oh... it seems like they decided that the problem was due to his wife's moral harassment...

31
00:03:14,402 --> 00:03:16,321
(Female) I want to say it's my fault! ?

32
00:03:16,404 --> 00:03:17,363
Enough!

33
00:03:17,447 --> 00:03:19,782
I didn't get a single yen, so there was no reward!

34
00:03:19,866 --> 00:03:21,492
Huh! ? Ah...

35
00:03:21,576 --> 00:03:25,747
Ah... Wait, Wait... (Sound of door opening and closing)

36
00:03:27,874 --> 00:03:32,337
(Rie) Ah, working for free again.

37
00:03:34,964 --> 00:03:38,676
What do you mean by Mr. Yamamoto quitting?

38
00:03:38,760 --> 00:03:41,262
(Rie) It was because the teacher was good at trial for traffic violations⸺

39
00:03:41,346 --> 00:03:43,014
My runaway legs are fast

40
00:03:43,097 --> 00:03:45,683
Well, it can't be helped if I can't even pay my salary.

41
00:03:45,767 --> 00:03:47,143
but…

42
00:03:47,227 --> 00:03:49,979
If Professor Yamamoto leaves, I will be the only lawyer.

43
00:03:50,063 --> 00:03:52,190
The survival of the office is in danger!

44
00:03:52,273 --> 00:03:53,274
Hey~

45
00:03:53,358 --> 00:03:58,363
If my predecessor saw Zero's current situation, he would cry.

46
00:04:00,782 --> 00:04:01,741
(sigh)

47
00:04:01,824 --> 00:04:04,035
I wish I'd at least won today's trial.

48
00:04:04,118 --> 00:04:06,829
No, but that is⸺

49
00:04:06,913 --> 00:04:11,042
Before the court session, there was a strange person and I got upset...

50
00:04:11,125 --> 00:04:12,585
Ah, that's right

51
00:04:12,669 --> 00:04:15,880
That strange person gave it to me.

52
00:04:16,464 --> 00:04:18,091
Sealing hand...

53
00:04:20,802 --> 00:04:21,803
Huh?

54
00:04:24,555 --> 00:04:28,685
 (Tatsuo) “Judgment dismissing the plaintiff’s claim”

55
00:04:29,269 --> 00:04:32,105
“Litigation costs shall be borne by the plaintiff.”

56
00:04:32,981 --> 00:04:35,566
“Facts and Reasons”

57
00:04:36,484 --> 00:04:38,444
 (Torataro) “Dismiss the claim”

58
00:04:38,528 --> 00:04:40,321
(Rie) Huh? Did you write this after hearing the verdict?

59
00:04:40,405 --> 00:04:43,324
Rather, it was given to me before the trial started.

60
00:04:43,408 --> 00:04:46,744
Huh? So does that mean you predicted the verdict in advance?

61
00:04:48,079 --> 00:04:51,165
(Torataro) Before the court session? Did you just read the material?

62
00:04:51,708 --> 00:04:55,128
(Door chime) (Rie) Ah, maybe a new request.

63
00:04:55,211 --> 00:04:56,045
(Torataro) Ah!

64
00:04:56,129 --> 00:04:59,549
Welcome to the trusted and proven Ayuda Law Office

65
00:05:00,550 --> 00:05:02,802
Ah, this in the daytime!

66
00:05:03,845 --> 00:05:05,138
(Rie) Lie...

67
00:05:08,182 --> 00:05:09,934
(Rie) Salted butter daifuku if you like.

68
00:05:10,018 --> 00:05:12,145
(Tatsumi) Ah, then I'll take your word for it.

69
00:05:28,578 --> 00:05:31,622
Really? Would you like to join our office?

70
00:05:31,706 --> 00:05:35,251
(Rie) Yeah, I posted a recruitment ad on the internet because it didn't work.

71
00:05:35,334 --> 00:05:37,670
I only got one reply.

72
00:05:37,754 --> 00:05:40,214
(Torataro) Tatsumi Tendo

73
00:05:42,300 --> 00:05:44,677
Do you have a lawyer qualification?

74
00:05:44,761 --> 00:05:48,181
(Tatsumi) Yes, registered with the Tokyo Central Bar Association.

75
00:05:48,890 --> 00:05:50,683
If what I said earlier is true⸺

76
00:05:50,767 --> 00:05:52,435
You're ready to help, right?

77
00:05:52,518 --> 00:05:53,353
Hiring decision

78
00:05:53,436 --> 00:05:55,313
...But is it okay to decide so easily?

79
00:05:55,396 --> 00:05:57,398
(Tatsumi) Um... if you don't mind⸺

80
00:05:58,066 --> 00:06:00,193
Whether I am suited to be a lawyer⸺

81
00:06:00,276 --> 00:06:02,278
Could you please give me a test?

82
00:06:02,945 --> 00:06:05,114
Did you pass the bar exam?

83
00:06:05,198 --> 00:06:07,784
There was also an exam to enter the encouragement group⸺

84
00:06:07,867 --> 00:06:10,953
I want you to take the exam to become a lawyer.

85
00:06:11,037 --> 00:06:11,996
Isn't it good? Even here⸺

86
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:13,206
Um... we need manpower.

87
00:06:13,289 --> 00:06:14,123
Hey, Kotaro-sensei

88
00:06:14,207 --> 00:06:16,042
-(Torataro) Huh? -(Tatsumi) Kotaro...

89
00:06:16,125 --> 00:06:19,337
(Rie) Ah, this is the director and lawyer of this office⸺

90
00:06:19,420 --> 00:06:21,798
My name is Torataro Ayuda.

91
00:06:21,881 --> 00:06:25,384
My father, who passed away, was the previous director, so that's his name.

92
00:06:25,468 --> 00:06:27,762
...I am a paralegal and an accountant.

93
00:06:27,845 --> 00:06:30,389
My name is Rie Inui. Nice to meet you.

94
00:06:30,473 --> 00:06:33,518
This is Tatsumi Tendo. Nice to meet you.

95
00:06:33,601 --> 00:06:34,769
(Torataro) Welcome

96
00:06:35,645 --> 00:06:36,479
yes

97
00:06:36,562 --> 00:06:38,147
Well, if you decide to do that

98
00:06:38,231 --> 00:06:40,525
Um... I'm asking you to use this desk.

99
00:06:40,608 --> 00:06:44,654
(Tatsumi) Ah, ah... If you don't mind, go over there.

100
00:06:48,825 --> 00:06:52,078
(Rie) No, uh... In the nap room when there were a lot of lawyers.

101
00:06:52,161 --> 00:06:53,454
It's like a storeroom now

102
00:06:53,538 --> 00:06:55,498
I don't mind it at all, though.

103
00:06:55,581 --> 00:06:57,416
Is it okay? In a place like this

104
00:06:57,500 --> 00:07:00,294
(Tatsumi) Yes, I'm more used to tatami.

105
00:07:01,254 --> 00:07:03,756
yes! I like tatami for proper bowing.

106
00:07:03,840 --> 00:07:06,134
Maybe they were offering tea or flowers?

107
00:07:06,217 --> 00:07:07,718
Ah, unexpectedly it turned out to be Karuta.

108
00:07:07,802 --> 00:07:08,886
-(Tatsumi) Ah, no... -(Rie) Ah, yes, that's right.

109
00:07:08,970 --> 00:07:10,972
I need to draw up a business outsourcing contract.

110
00:07:11,055 --> 00:07:12,640
(Torataro) Understood.

111
00:07:15,893 --> 00:07:17,437
It's shogi

112
00:07:29,031 --> 00:07:30,074
(Tatsuo) Ah...

113
00:07:30,158 --> 00:07:31,033
 (Kasumi) If you are interested⸺

114
00:07:31,117 --> 00:07:32,577
Why don't you go directly to your room?

115
00:07:32,660 --> 00:07:34,287
(Tatsuo) No, but as soon as you come back⸺

116
00:07:34,370 --> 00:07:36,747
I suddenly went straight to my room.

117
00:07:36,831 --> 00:07:40,042
I guess I wasn't cut out to be a lawyer after all.

118
00:07:40,126 --> 00:07:41,919
What if Tatsuo-san follows me?

119
00:07:42,003 --> 00:07:44,797
When Tatsumi is the agent, a favorable judgment will be issued.

120
00:07:44,881 --> 00:07:47,175
If you mix up your private life like that, you will be punished.

121
00:07:47,967 --> 00:07:52,597
Ryumi can handle any situation.

122
00:08:06,194 --> 00:08:10,406
All that's left is the pieces...

123
00:08:38,809 --> 00:08:40,394
(Torataro) Good morning.

124
00:08:42,104 --> 00:08:43,397
What's wrong?

125
00:08:44,607 --> 00:08:46,651
No, Tatsumi Tendo-sensei?

126
00:08:46,734 --> 00:08:51,322
I brought in a lot of luggage, even this square thing.

127
00:08:51,405 --> 00:08:52,615
Isn't it a PC or something?

128
00:08:52,698 --> 00:08:53,783
No, that's different.

129
00:08:53,866 --> 00:08:55,576
Huh? (phone ringtone)

130
00:08:56,244 --> 00:08:59,872
Yes, Ayuda Law Office can handle anything now.

131
00:09:00,998 --> 00:09:01,832
request! ?

132
00:09:03,459 --> 00:09:04,877
-(Rie) It's here! -(Torataro) Yay!

133
00:09:05,461 --> 00:09:06,379
Finally⸺

134
00:09:07,004 --> 00:09:09,548
It's the first game

135
00:09:10,216 --> 00:09:12,218
♪～

136
00:09:22,395 --> 00:09:24,397
～♪

137
00:09:26,983 --> 00:09:29,902
Have you been a victim of unwanted goods purchase?

138
00:09:29,986 --> 00:09:32,363
 (Kinuko) Yeah, about six months ago.

139
00:09:32,446 --> 00:09:33,531
(Rie) That's it⸺

140
00:09:33,614 --> 00:09:34,782
Go inside the house⸺

141
00:09:34,865 --> 00:09:36,450
Even important things that I have no intention of selling⸺

142
00:09:36,534 --> 00:09:37,868
Isn't it something you should take with you?

143
00:09:37,952 --> 00:09:39,412
(Kinuko) That's right.

144
00:09:39,495 --> 00:09:44,292
Um... In the house where I've lived with my family all my life⸺

145
00:09:44,375 --> 00:09:46,752
I live alone now.

146
00:09:46,836 --> 00:09:49,755
(Kirioka) Hey grandma, you don't need this watch, right?

147
00:09:49,839 --> 00:09:52,675
(Kinuko) Huh? Wait... I'm having a bit of trouble. That's...

148
00:09:52,758 --> 00:09:55,177
- (Kirioka) Purchase decision - (Kinuko) As a memento of the owner.

149
00:09:55,261 --> 00:09:59,056
(Kirioka) Oh, this camera is nice too.

150
00:09:59,140 --> 00:10:02,226
(Kinuko) Don't even listen to what I say, just forcefully

151
00:10:02,310 --> 00:10:04,562
Um... please listen to me.

152
00:10:04,645 --> 00:10:07,815
In that case, first report the damage to the police...

153
00:10:07,898 --> 00:10:11,152
(Kinuko) No, if it's the culprit, he's already been caught.

154
00:10:11,235 --> 00:10:12,236
Huh?

155
00:10:13,988 --> 00:10:18,784
(Rie) Yuya Kirioka, 25 years old, “arrested on suspicion of theft”

156
00:10:18,868 --> 00:10:21,746
He has been sentenced to a suspended sentence.

157
00:10:21,829 --> 00:10:24,540
So wouldn't the stolen items have been returned?

158
00:10:24,624 --> 00:10:25,916
There wasn't.

159
00:10:26,000 --> 00:10:29,920
Everything else was there, but this was the only one

160
00:10:31,047 --> 00:10:32,590
This is it

161
00:10:32,673 --> 00:10:34,925
(Rie) Ah, what a wonderful accessory case.

162
00:10:35,009 --> 00:10:37,595
Is this a very valuable item?

163
00:10:37,678 --> 00:10:39,555
(Kinuko) I often talk about prices...

164
00:10:39,639 --> 00:10:45,519
But it's a keepsake that my late husband gave me.

165
00:10:46,312 --> 00:10:50,399
I want the court to give it back to me.

166
00:10:50,483 --> 00:10:55,446
Um... I also brought documents from the previous trial.

167
00:10:55,946 --> 00:11:01,702
In other words, a lawsuit seeking the return of items taken in the theft of unwanted items.

168
00:11:03,704 --> 00:11:06,165
What do you think, Mr. Ryumi?

169
00:11:06,248 --> 00:11:09,168
I agree…

170
00:11:34,777 --> 00:11:35,903
that…

171
00:11:36,946 --> 00:11:38,406
- (Tatsumi) Ah... - (Torataro) What are you doing?

172
00:11:38,489 --> 00:11:40,741
(Tatsumi) Sorry, it's just a habit.

173
00:11:41,534 --> 00:11:45,121
I think it would be better to think about it long enough to answer properly.

174
00:11:45,204 --> 00:11:46,205
Chokou?

175
00:11:46,288 --> 00:11:50,376
Assuming that the other party does not have the damaged goods on hand⸺

176
00:11:50,459 --> 00:11:53,963
It is legally difficult to request a refund.

177
00:11:54,046 --> 00:11:57,925
In that case, the best option is to seek monetary compensation.

178
00:11:58,008 --> 00:12:00,803
The problem is Kosaka-san⸺

179
00:12:00,886 --> 00:12:05,391
This is a point that has been negotiated with the defendant, Mr. Kirioka.

180
00:12:06,016 --> 00:12:06,934
Huh?

181
00:12:11,564 --> 00:12:13,774
Ah... the settlement was reached...

182
00:12:13,858 --> 00:12:16,360
(Kinuko) I didn't think so⸺

183
00:12:16,444 --> 00:12:18,779
My son did it without my knowledge⸺

184
00:12:18,863 --> 00:12:22,032
I ended up talking with the other party's lawyer...

185
00:12:22,116 --> 00:12:25,828
The other party will probably argue that the claim is not valid.

186
00:12:27,079 --> 00:12:29,623
I think it will be difficult to win

187
00:12:29,707 --> 00:12:32,418
I really want it back

188
00:12:32,501 --> 00:12:37,339
Um... please, please!

189
00:12:47,475 --> 00:12:51,479
This Yuya Kirioka is just the perpetrator⸺

190
00:12:51,562 --> 00:12:53,022
Recycle shop in the back⸺

191
00:12:53,105 --> 00:12:55,107
My name is Kazuto Maruhashi, the store manager⸺

192
00:12:55,191 --> 00:12:57,109
Looks like there was a main culprit.

193
00:12:57,193 --> 00:12:58,819
 (Torataro) That round bridge too⸺

194
00:12:58,903 --> 00:13:00,905
Oh, he's guilty and his sentence is suspended.

195
00:13:00,988 --> 00:13:02,656
(Rie) Hmm.

196
00:13:04,492 --> 00:13:06,827
Oh, this criminal trial defense⸺

197
00:13:06,911 --> 00:13:09,413
Seventh Rank Law Office is in charge.

198
00:13:09,497 --> 00:13:10,664
(Torataro) That major law firm?

199
00:13:10,748 --> 00:13:13,167
- (Rie) Yeah, yeah - (Torataro) Ah, I'm going to be a detective.

200
00:13:13,250 --> 00:13:16,378
Ah, Yuya Kirioka's father is⸺

201
00:13:16,462 --> 00:13:19,089
Because I am a director of a major precision equipment manufacturer⸺

202
00:13:19,173 --> 00:13:20,883
Maybe he accepted it through connections.

203
00:13:20,966 --> 00:13:23,636
Honestly, the chances of winning are slim, but⸺

204
00:13:23,719 --> 00:13:27,890
Is it okay if I accept this?

205
00:13:29,308 --> 00:13:30,768
Because!

206
00:13:31,352 --> 00:13:33,812
Mr. Kosaka is a victim in the first place.

207
00:13:34,605 --> 00:13:37,066
I want to help you somehow, don't you?

208
00:13:37,149 --> 00:13:39,026
Client first is good too⸺

209
00:13:39,109 --> 00:13:42,279
After reaching a settlement, I will request the return of the goods⸺

210
00:13:42,363 --> 00:13:46,700
As far as I can see, there are very few similar cases in the past.

211
00:13:47,284 --> 00:13:49,912
Mr. Torataro, please stay with me.

212
00:13:49,995 --> 00:13:51,121
yes?

213
00:13:51,205 --> 00:13:55,334
The trial is faster than the profit or loss of the pieces.Let's go.

214
00:13:55,417 --> 00:13:58,128
Huh? Ah... yes yes?

215
00:13:58,212 --> 00:13:59,922
Ah, wait a minute...

216
00:14:00,005 --> 00:14:03,300
A frame? Chokou?

217
00:14:05,678 --> 00:14:08,013
By any chance...

218
00:14:08,097 --> 00:14:11,767
(Typing sound) (Rie) Eh~ Tatsumi Tendo...

219
00:14:13,894 --> 00:14:15,062
fault!

220
00:14:15,646 --> 00:14:16,564
(Sound of door opening) (Tatsumi) I’m home.

221
00:14:16,647 --> 00:14:18,857
(Tatsuo) Welcome back Tatsumi, you're early...

222
00:14:19,525 --> 00:14:20,734
judge! ?

223
00:14:20,818 --> 00:14:22,194
(sound of door closing)

224
00:14:22,278 --> 00:14:24,864
“Dismiss the plaintiff’s claim”

225
00:14:24,947 --> 00:14:27,116
-(Tatsuo) Huh? Huh! ? -(Torataro) Huh? Huh! ?

226
00:14:27,199 --> 00:14:28,534
(Tatsumi) My father was in charge before⸺

227
00:14:28,617 --> 00:14:32,288
I would like to see the materials for the item return request case.

228
00:14:32,371 --> 00:14:35,374
Ah, please come up.

229
00:14:35,457 --> 00:14:39,461
(Torataro) Ah, yes, then I'm in the way...

230
00:14:44,300 --> 00:14:48,846
I didn't realize that your father was a judge...

231
00:14:48,929 --> 00:14:50,639
(Kasumi) Oh, oh, don't be so nervous⸺

232
00:14:50,723 --> 00:14:52,933
Please make it easier

233
00:14:53,017 --> 00:14:55,603
It's not a court, so don't worry about it.

234
00:14:55,686 --> 00:14:58,689
He's the director of the office that Tatsumi takes care of.

235
00:14:58,772 --> 00:15:01,483
As a judge, outside the courtroom⸺

236
00:15:01,567 --> 00:15:03,986
Unnecessarily sharing a seat with a lawyer⸺

237
00:15:04,069 --> 00:15:06,280
Is it morally wrong?

238
00:15:06,363 --> 00:15:08,198
If you know Ryumi in private⸺

239
00:15:08,282 --> 00:15:09,241
There's no problem, right?

240
00:15:09,325 --> 00:15:12,828
(Tatsuo) Private? Is that a relationship already?

241
00:15:12,912 --> 00:15:14,246
No, no, no, I'm just talking to Ryumi-sensei⸺

242
00:15:14,330 --> 00:15:15,497
Just being asked to "hang out"...

243
00:15:15,581 --> 00:15:16,415
Let's hang out! ?

244
00:15:16,498 --> 00:15:19,960
(Kasumi) Tatsumi What are you doing? Don't even talk to the director.

245
00:15:20,044 --> 00:15:21,795
It's okay!

246
00:15:22,671 --> 00:15:24,006
Did you find anything?

247
00:15:24,089 --> 00:15:25,424
(Tatsumi) In a case similar to this time⸺

248
00:15:25,507 --> 00:15:27,843
There was a court precedent that invalidated a settlement.

249
00:15:28,469 --> 00:15:31,639
How to accept a claim for the return of stolen items⸺

250
00:15:31,722 --> 00:15:35,392
At the time of the settlement, there was proof that the defendant had a hidden accessory case.

251
00:15:35,476 --> 00:15:36,644
seems essential

252
00:15:36,727 --> 00:15:40,272
But if you can prove it, you might win.

253
00:15:40,356 --> 00:15:42,775
Please show that document to Rie-san tomorrow.

254
00:15:42,858 --> 00:15:45,736
I've already memorized it, so I'll spend the night studying it.

255
00:15:51,158 --> 00:15:52,159
Huh?

256
00:15:54,411 --> 00:15:56,872
Have you learned this yet?

257
00:15:57,498 --> 00:15:58,874
Okay

258
00:16:06,465 --> 00:16:07,841
I'm going home

259
00:16:07,925 --> 00:16:10,427
(Kasumi) Oh, are you home yet? If you like, we can have dinner

260
00:16:10,511 --> 00:16:11,679
Oh, that's unbelievable, I got in the way!

261
00:16:11,762 --> 00:16:13,055
Eh, no... don't hold back.

262
00:16:13,138 --> 00:16:13,972
(Torataro) No, no, it's really okay!

263
00:16:14,056 --> 00:16:14,890
(Kasumi) Is that so?

264
00:16:14,974 --> 00:16:15,808
(Torataro) Thank you very much.

265
00:16:15,891 --> 00:16:17,101
(Kasumi) Even though I came all the way.

266
00:16:17,184 --> 00:16:19,395
Did Ryumi say “go out with me”?

267
00:16:19,895 --> 00:16:23,440
No way...

268
00:16:24,191 --> 00:16:26,110
 (Akinobu) Because of my stupid son⸺

269
00:16:26,193 --> 00:16:28,320
I have troubled you many times⸺

270
00:16:28,404 --> 00:16:29,321
I'm sorry.

271
00:16:29,405 --> 00:16:31,198
 (Ochiai) No, no, the managing director⸺

272
00:16:31,281 --> 00:16:33,784
Thank you for your help on a daily basis.

273
00:16:34,952 --> 00:16:37,454
(Ochiai) It's a trial that seems like an accusation.

274
00:16:37,538 --> 00:16:39,540
I'll finish it right away

275
00:16:39,623 --> 00:16:40,708
 (Akinobu) From my side too⸺

276
00:16:40,791 --> 00:16:43,252
Call Fushitomo Shoji⸺

277
00:16:43,335 --> 00:16:46,004
I'll finish the rooting.

278
00:16:46,088 --> 00:16:47,673
(Ochiai) That's helpful.

279
00:17:04,857 --> 00:17:06,567
(Torataro) Shogi?

280
00:17:06,650 --> 00:17:08,152
-(Torataro) Mr. Ryumi? -(Rie) Yeah.

281
00:17:08,235 --> 00:17:10,320
It wasn't written on the entry sheet⸺

282
00:17:10,404 --> 00:17:11,447
I looked it up

283
00:17:11,530 --> 00:17:13,031
 (Sound of keys being pressed) (Rie) Look.

284
00:17:13,115 --> 00:17:17,244
(Torataro) Shogi Federation Encouragement Group 3rd Dan?

285
00:17:17,327 --> 00:17:18,954
Why become a lawyer?

286
00:17:19,038 --> 00:17:21,039
No, look, it's an encouragement meeting⸺

287
00:17:21,123 --> 00:17:23,834
There is an age limit and by what age you have to reach a certain rank⸺

288
00:17:23,917 --> 00:17:25,335
Will it be automatically stopped?

289
00:17:25,419 --> 00:17:27,129
It seems like there are all kinds of things like that.

290
00:17:27,212 --> 00:17:33,594
(Torataro) Hmm, in short, I gave up being a professional shogi player and became a lawyer.

291
00:17:33,677 --> 00:17:36,764
Well, wouldn't it be perfect as a second career?

292
00:17:36,847 --> 00:17:40,476
But no matter how good you are at shogi, are you really suited to be a lawyer?

293
00:17:40,559 --> 00:17:42,311
Is that okay?

294
00:17:43,145 --> 00:17:44,271
- (Torataro) Yes - (Tatsumi) Um...

295
00:17:44,354 --> 00:17:48,525
This is in the record of the trial in which Mr. Kirioka was given a suspended sentence.

296
00:17:49,359 --> 00:17:51,737
(Torataro) What is the history of the sites you access on your smartphone?

297
00:17:51,820 --> 00:17:54,948
(Tatsumi) When I went to that site, I saw a page like this.

298
00:17:55,032 --> 00:17:56,825
(Rie) An overseas auction site?

299
00:17:56,909 --> 00:18:00,287
(Tatsumi) Doesn't it look similar to what Kinuko Kosaka is asking for back?

300
00:18:00,370 --> 00:18:04,666
“Trinket case made by 19th century Spanish craftsman Remiro”

301
00:18:04,750 --> 00:18:06,418
-(Rie) Market value 5 million! ? - (Torataro) Oh!

302
00:18:06,502 --> 00:18:09,713
Mr. Kirioka saw this site and found the accessory case he stole⸺

303
00:18:09,797 --> 00:18:12,674
In fact, if you realized that you could sell it at a high price...

304
00:18:12,758 --> 00:18:14,718
The main culprit is the Maruhashi recycling shop⸺

305
00:18:14,802 --> 00:18:17,846
Maybe he was trying to stealth it by himself without giving it to me.

306
00:18:17,930 --> 00:18:19,807
Only this accessory case was not returned⸺

307
00:18:19,890 --> 00:18:21,308
This may support the reason

308
00:18:21,391 --> 00:18:22,559
(Rie) I see.

309
00:18:36,240 --> 00:18:38,951
(Kasumi) Is it okay? The judge came to the audience.

310
00:18:39,034 --> 00:18:41,912
No, because it's Ryumi's courtroom debut⸺

311
00:18:41,995 --> 00:18:43,580
I can't afford to miss it

312
00:18:43,664 --> 00:18:45,415
(Secretary) Please stand up.

313
00:18:52,756 --> 00:18:59,304
Item Return Request Event No. 1248 in Reiwa 6 Years

314
00:18:59,388 --> 00:19:06,228
Plaintiff A Kinuko Kosaka Defendant B Yuya Kirioka

315
00:19:06,311 --> 00:19:09,231
(Judge) Will the plaintiff state the complaint?

316
00:19:09,940 --> 00:19:12,109
Yes, I will make a statement

317
00:19:12,192 --> 00:19:14,570
Will the defendant file a response?

318
00:19:14,653 --> 00:19:16,780
Yes, I will make a statement

319
00:19:17,573 --> 00:19:20,284
(Judge) From the plaintiff to Part A... (Sekibarai)

320
00:19:20,367 --> 00:19:21,827
It may be confusing at first⸺

321
00:19:21,910 --> 00:19:26,039
In the case of civil cases, the first date is the statement of the complaint and answer.

322
00:19:26,123 --> 00:19:29,710
All you have to do is specify the next date and do other clerical work.

323
00:19:29,793 --> 00:19:32,671
In other words, it's the set of pieces at the beginning of the game.

324
00:19:32,754 --> 00:19:34,381
Koma… Komagumi?

325
00:19:37,301 --> 00:19:41,263
(Rie) What? There are five lawyers there.

326
00:19:48,478 --> 00:19:50,063
(Judge) Well, the next date is...

327
00:19:50,147 --> 00:19:55,819
A ball is surrounded by five pieces: two gold pieces, a silver horse, and a car.

328
00:19:55,903 --> 00:19:56,778
this is…

329
00:19:56,862 --> 00:19:59,823
(Judge) Well, that's it for today.

330
00:20:04,745 --> 00:20:05,871
This formation is...

331
00:20:05,954 --> 00:20:07,789
(Torataro) What have you been muttering about for a while now?

332
00:20:07,873 --> 00:20:14,630
I could see what kind of trajectory this trial would lead to.

333
00:20:23,555 --> 00:20:24,473
Badger?

334
00:20:25,474 --> 00:20:28,018
Ah, ah... Before I knew it...

335
00:20:28,101 --> 00:20:29,353
Wow~

336
00:20:29,436 --> 00:20:34,149
What is Shogi? First move and second move⸺

337
00:20:34,232 --> 00:20:37,486
Take turns moving the pieces one move at a time⸺

338
00:20:37,569 --> 00:20:41,657
The one who takes the opponent's ball king first wins.

339
00:20:41,740 --> 00:20:42,574
Huh? From there?

340
00:20:42,658 --> 00:20:47,579
(Tatsumi) There are various strategies in shogi⸺

341
00:20:47,663 --> 00:20:49,623
What is this anaguma?

342
00:20:49,706 --> 00:20:52,334
Far from the battlefield⸺

343
00:20:52,417 --> 00:20:56,880
Move the king to this end⸺

344
00:20:56,964 --> 00:21:01,343
Kosha Keima Protect it with silver and two pieces of gold⸺

345
00:21:01,426 --> 00:21:04,763
This is the strategy with the strongest defensive power.

346
00:21:05,597 --> 00:21:06,682
yes

347
00:21:07,641 --> 00:21:10,644
What does this have to do with this trial?

348
00:21:10,727 --> 00:21:14,314
The defendant's father is a director of a major precision equipment manufacturer.

349
00:21:14,398 --> 00:21:16,817
The agent is a lawyer from a famous law firm.

350
00:21:16,900 --> 00:21:21,571
A perfectly defensive formation is exactly like an anaguma enclosure.

351
00:21:24,908 --> 00:21:26,159
For such a person...

352
00:21:26,743 --> 00:21:29,246
We also strengthen our defense⸺

353
00:21:30,455 --> 00:21:34,960
The most reliable strategy is to bring it to Aianaguma.

354
00:21:37,504 --> 00:21:41,717
Aianaguma seems to be a strategy that emphasizes defense⸺

355
00:21:41,800 --> 00:21:44,344
When the pieces start colliding⸺

356
00:21:44,428 --> 00:21:47,431
This often leads to fierce battles.

357
00:21:48,348 --> 00:21:50,976
Attacking piece equals witness

358
00:21:51,059 --> 00:21:55,814
In other words, the question is how strong a witness can be brought onto the board.

359
00:21:55,897 --> 00:21:57,357
It will be the difference between winning and losing

360
00:21:57,441 --> 00:22:01,570
(Torataro) No, I understand that, but why do you talk about everything using shogi?

361
00:22:01,653 --> 00:22:02,946
In order to win this lawsuit

362
00:22:03,030 --> 00:22:06,116
That's why that accessory case was so expensive⸺

363
00:22:06,199 --> 00:22:08,702
I need to find a witness to testify.

364
00:22:09,411 --> 00:22:11,913
First, let's go to Kosaka-san's place.

365
00:22:11,997 --> 00:22:14,833
I even decide the policy on my own.

366
00:22:14,916 --> 00:22:17,127
Look, I thought this was part of the test.

367
00:22:17,210 --> 00:22:18,336
Come on!

368
00:22:18,420 --> 00:22:19,755
(Torataro) I... I understand.

369
00:22:19,838 --> 00:22:21,798
(Kinuko) What is the story?

370
00:22:22,382 --> 00:22:24,885
Do you know the store where you bought that accessory case?

371
00:22:24,968 --> 00:22:26,345
Ah...

372
00:22:26,428 --> 00:22:27,888
sorry

373
00:22:27,971 --> 00:22:30,223
When my son was born⸺

374
00:22:30,307 --> 00:22:33,685
My husband bought it for me as a celebration⸺

375
00:22:33,769 --> 00:22:35,896
As far as where I bought it...

376
00:22:35,979 --> 00:22:39,983
Is there someone who can testify to what you value?

377
00:22:40,567 --> 00:22:43,445
I wonder if anyone was there

378
00:22:50,535 --> 00:22:53,455
(Hiroki) Will I be the witness in the trial?

379
00:22:53,538 --> 00:22:56,958
(Tatsumi) Yes, the plaintiff's son is the strongest piece.

380
00:22:57,042 --> 00:22:58,794
Don't say "piece"

381
00:22:58,877 --> 00:23:00,295
(Tatsumi) Ah... I'm sorry.

382
00:23:00,378 --> 00:23:02,297
Hiroki-san until 8 years ago⸺

383
00:23:02,381 --> 00:23:03,382
At that house with Kinuko⸺

384
00:23:03,465 --> 00:23:04,925
You lived there, right?

385
00:23:05,008 --> 00:23:06,093
Yeah

386
00:23:06,176 --> 00:23:07,969
In this house when my daughter was born

387
00:23:08,053 --> 00:23:10,472
(Torataro) If so, then your mother Kinuko⸺

388
00:23:10,555 --> 00:23:13,517
How much did you cherish that accessory case⸺

389
00:23:13,600 --> 00:23:15,769
Could you testify?

390
00:23:15,852 --> 00:23:18,772
Even if you say that, I still have work to do on weekdays...

391
00:23:18,855 --> 00:23:20,315
(Satoko) It's impossible.

392
00:23:20,398 --> 00:23:22,692
(Satoko) That person's company is everything.

393
00:23:22,776 --> 00:23:24,778
It's Himari's school event⸺

394
00:23:24,861 --> 00:23:26,780
He has never come out.

395
00:23:26,863 --> 00:23:28,406
(Hiroki) Satoko: Okay, in front of the lawyer.

396
00:23:28,490 --> 00:23:30,617
(Satoko) I can see the lawyer now⸺

397
00:23:30,700 --> 00:23:33,537
Why don't we talk about that too?

398
00:23:35,080 --> 00:23:37,916
Ah, wait... If I don't go now, I'll be late for cram school.

399
00:23:40,710 --> 00:23:43,338
Um...the story over there...

400
00:23:43,422 --> 00:23:44,548
Understood

401
00:23:44,631 --> 00:23:49,136
I will explain the circumstances to the company and try to arrange a time for you to appear in court.

402
00:23:49,719 --> 00:23:51,721
(Tatsumi/Torataro) Thank you

403
00:23:57,936 --> 00:24:00,647
(Rie) I'm glad you found the pieces to fight with Aianaguma.

404
00:24:00,730 --> 00:24:04,943
(Torataro) Huh... Rie-san doesn't need to be compared to shogi.

405
00:24:05,026 --> 00:24:07,404
This proves that that accessory case is worth it⸺

406
00:24:07,487 --> 00:24:09,489
I can get you to testify.

407
00:24:09,573 --> 00:24:12,701
The important thing is that Kirioka is hiding something⸺

408
00:24:12,784 --> 00:24:14,661
I can't prove it yet.

409
00:24:20,584 --> 00:24:25,422
If the second defendant actively comes after Anaguma completes each other⸺

410
00:24:26,006 --> 00:24:27,924
35 steps

411
00:24:28,008 --> 00:24:30,552
The battle begins from here.

412
00:24:30,635 --> 00:24:33,889
(Torataro) Ah, he's seriously playing shogi.

413
00:24:33,972 --> 00:24:37,684
No, the correct answer is to play Go and to “point” in Shogi.

414
00:24:39,895 --> 00:24:40,854
Ah...

415
00:24:41,646 --> 00:24:43,940
(Judge) Conducts a personal identification examination

416
00:24:44,024 --> 00:24:46,985
Address Name Occupation Age is⸺

417
00:24:47,068 --> 00:24:49,946
Is it as written on the witness card?

418
00:24:50,030 --> 00:24:51,656
(Hiroki) Yes, definitely.

419
00:24:51,740 --> 00:24:55,243
The plaintiff's powerful witness is a big piece.

420
00:24:55,911 --> 00:24:58,872
The one move that will break down the impregnable Anaguma is⸺

421
00:24:58,955 --> 00:25:00,749
1 a speeding car

422
00:25:00,832 --> 00:25:03,043
(Judge) Please begin the main examination.

423
00:25:03,126 --> 00:25:04,169
yes

424
00:25:06,796 --> 00:25:10,008
Plaintiff's attorney Ayuda will ask a question.

425
00:25:10,967 --> 00:25:13,970
I will show you this photo of Exhibit A No. 18.

426
00:25:15,263 --> 00:25:18,725
You know this accessory case pictured here, right?

427
00:25:18,808 --> 00:25:21,478
Yes, I remember leaving it at my parents' house for a long time.

428
00:25:21,561 --> 00:25:24,648
Plaintiff, in other words, your mother⸺

429
00:25:24,731 --> 00:25:27,734
Did you cherish this accessory case?

430
00:25:27,817 --> 00:25:32,072
I don't think he particularly valued it.

431
00:25:35,408 --> 00:25:38,828
...But my late father was given to my mother⸺

432
00:25:38,912 --> 00:25:41,539
Wasn't it an expensive item?

433
00:25:41,623 --> 00:25:43,667
My father is not a connoisseur or anything like that⸺

434
00:25:43,750 --> 00:25:47,170
By the time I left the house, it was gathering dust on the shelf.

435
00:25:47,254 --> 00:25:50,382
This doesn't point to Trap 1 and the Rook on the draw...

436
00:25:50,465 --> 00:25:51,591
(Hiroki) Embarrassing story⸺

437
00:25:51,675 --> 00:25:54,344
My mother seems to have become a little out of touch lately.

438
00:25:54,427 --> 00:25:56,846
Even if I talk about my daughter or wife⸺

439
00:25:56,930 --> 00:25:59,266
I keep getting misguided answers.

440
00:25:59,349 --> 00:26:03,603
I lost that accessory case at an unexpected time.

441
00:26:03,687 --> 00:26:05,981
You may have mistakenly thought that it was taken.

442
00:26:06,064 --> 00:26:10,068
Ah... what the heck...

443
00:26:10,151 --> 00:26:11,987
Far from destroying Anaguma⸺

444
00:26:12,612 --> 00:26:16,324
This one has lost its big piece, the rook.

445
00:26:16,992 --> 00:26:18,535
(Torataro) That's it for the interrogation.

446
00:26:20,620 --> 00:26:26,459
(Tatsumi) It was a completely bad move and it was written as “bad move”.

447
00:26:33,300 --> 00:26:34,801
(Rie) My son Hiroki⸺

448
00:26:34,884 --> 00:26:39,681
I was in charge of precision equipment in the third sales section of Fukyo Shoji.

449
00:26:39,764 --> 00:26:41,266
At Hiroki's house⸺

450
00:26:41,349 --> 00:26:45,520
There was a pamphlet for the defendant's father's precision equipment manufacturer⸺

451
00:26:46,104 --> 00:26:47,897
I didn't read enough

452
00:26:47,981 --> 00:26:49,316
(Rie) Well, today's testimony too⸺

453
00:26:49,399 --> 00:26:53,028
If Hiroki really thought that Kinuko didn't take good care of her⸺

454
00:26:53,111 --> 00:26:54,529
It's not perjury

455
00:26:54,613 --> 00:26:56,448
For the defendant to have an advantage⸺

456
00:26:56,531 --> 00:27:00,201
There's no evidence that it was included.

457
00:27:01,244 --> 00:27:03,538
(Tatsumi) To put the current situation in terms of evaluation value⸺

458
00:27:03,622 --> 00:27:08,376
I guess it's 30% for me and 70% for the other party.

459
00:27:08,460 --> 00:27:11,338
Does this mean that the chance of winning is 30%?

460
00:27:11,421 --> 00:27:15,008
Maybe you should consider withdrawing the lawsuit.

461
00:27:15,091 --> 00:27:18,678
An evaluation value of 30% is at a slightly disadvantageous level.

462
00:27:18,762 --> 00:27:19,971
There is still a chance of a turnaround.

463
00:27:20,055 --> 00:27:21,556
There's a difference between shogi and a trial.

464
00:27:23,058 --> 00:27:25,310
People are not pawns either.

465
00:27:27,270 --> 00:27:30,190
His son Hiroki has joined the defendant's side.

466
00:27:31,399 --> 00:27:35,403
If things go wrong, parent and child might end up in a fight.

467
00:27:36,154 --> 00:27:37,739
(Rie) As Hiroki said⸺

468
00:27:37,822 --> 00:27:42,619
I can't deny the possibility that Kinuko-san was mistaken.

469
00:27:43,453 --> 00:27:45,330
(Kinuko) I'm sorry.

470
00:27:48,708 --> 00:27:51,002
...even if I am

471
00:27:54,673 --> 00:27:58,510
You can't concede when you still have a chance to win.

472
00:28:04,724 --> 00:28:10,271
(Rie) Oh, he himself went into the cave.

473
00:28:10,355 --> 00:28:11,981
Mr. Ryumi!

474
00:28:12,065 --> 00:28:13,358
knock)

475
00:28:13,441 --> 00:28:15,318
(Rie) Dr. Ryumi

476
00:28:15,985 --> 00:28:18,822
What is it already?

477
00:28:18,905 --> 00:28:22,450
Hey, maybe this will pass the recruitment exam.

478
00:28:22,534 --> 00:28:24,369
Isn't it good?

479
00:28:24,452 --> 00:28:26,830
They were the ones who asked me to take the test.

480
00:28:33,211 --> 00:28:35,213
My predecessor, Yojiro Sensei

481
00:28:35,296 --> 00:28:39,050
It looks like my office will be the only lawyer again.

482
00:28:50,979 --> 00:28:53,148
Delicious (door chime)

483
00:28:53,231 --> 00:28:54,482
yes

484
00:28:56,234 --> 00:28:58,695
Yeah? Yeah! ?

485
00:28:59,654 --> 00:29:00,947
Yeah?

486
00:29:01,823 --> 00:29:05,535
(Torataro) I'm sorry, but you suddenly barged in at night.

487
00:29:06,453 --> 00:29:08,121
(Tatsuo) Alone?

488
00:29:10,498 --> 00:29:14,377
(Tatsuo) I see, Tatsumi got caged.

489
00:29:15,462 --> 00:29:20,800
Tatsumi: When it comes to competition, I hate losing more than anyone else.

490
00:29:21,301 --> 00:29:26,139
...Even so, it's a little hard to be so obsessed with winning.

491
00:29:26,806 --> 00:29:28,349
I can't help it

492
00:29:28,433 --> 00:29:29,976
That kid is⸺

493
00:29:30,059 --> 00:29:34,022
I've lived in a world where all I want is to win.

494
00:29:35,190 --> 00:29:38,443
That's the encouragement group...

495
00:29:39,861 --> 00:29:41,654
(Tatsuo) It's hard just to join⸺

496
00:29:41,738 --> 00:29:43,198
Starting from 6th grade⸺

497
00:29:43,281 --> 00:29:46,993
